<!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">

<font FACE="TimesNewRoman,Bold"><b>
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">&nbsp;</p>
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><a href="16.htm">
<img border="0" src="previous.gif" width="26" height="26"></a></p>
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><font size="7">Firefly </font> </p>
</b></font><!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
  <!--msthemelist--><tr>
    <!--msthemelist--><td valign="baseline" width="42">
    <img src="inmbul1a.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13" alt="bullet"></td>
    <td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><font size="5" face="Agency FB">In Firefly, temporal composition is expressed in terms of 
relations between instants (beginning and ending of objects and user 
interactions). </font> </p>
    <!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td>
  </tr>
  <!--msthemelist--><tr>
    <!--msthemelist--><td valign="baseline" width="42">
    <img src="inmbul1a.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13" alt="bullet"></td>
    <td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><font size="5" face="Agency FB">This is the first work in the constraint-based area that has 
considered the unpredictable nature of some multimedia objects (like user 
interactions) (issue 5).</font></p>
    <!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td>
  </tr>
  <!--msthemelist--></table>
<!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><font size="5" face="Agency FB">Working:</font></p>
<!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
  <!--msthemelist--><tr>
    <!--msthemelist--><td valign="baseline" width="42">
    <img src="inmbul1a.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13" alt="bullet"></td>
    <td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><font size="5" face="Agency FB">&nbsp;In order to provide a static formatting process 
handling this kind of objects, the Firefly scheduler partitions the temporal 
scenario at compile-time by grouping connected components (i. e. instants 
related by a temporal relation or a predictable duration). </font> </p>
    <!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td>
  </tr>
  <!--msthemelist--><tr>
    <!--msthemelist--><td valign="baseline" width="42">
    <img src="inmbul1a.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13" alt="bullet"></td>
    <td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><font size="5" face="Agency FB">Figure 10 shows the Firefly description of the Mascot 
scenario: there are two sets of connected components and two unpredictable 
objects (Button and Message) which appear with a dotted line. </font> </p>
    <!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td>
  </tr>
  <!--msthemelist--><tr>
    <!--msthemelist--><td valign="baseline" width="42">
    <img src="inmbul1a.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13" alt="bullet"></td>
    <td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><font size="5" face="Agency FB">The simplex algorithm is used to independently find the 
optimal solution of each partition. An event-driven scheduler dynamically 
handles the integration of the partitions. </font>
</p>
    <!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td>
  </tr>
  <!--msthemelist--></table>
<!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><font size="5" face="Agency FB"><img border="0" src="18.htm3.gif" width="619" height="327"></font></p>
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><font size="5" face="Agency FB">Disadvantages:</font></p>
<!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
  <!--msthemelist--><tr>
    <!--msthemelist--><td valign="baseline" width="42">
    <img src="inmbul1a.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13" alt="bullet"></td>
    <td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><font size="5" face="Agency FB">Unfortunately, the time performances of this batch process is 
not good-enough  in a interactive and incremental context (issue 12). This is 
the most important drawback of the Firefly approach. </font>
</p>
    <!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td>
  </tr>
  <!--msthemelist--><tr>
    <!--msthemelist--><td valign="baseline" width="42">
    <img src="inmbul1a.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13" alt="bullet"></td>
    <td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">
<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><font size="5" face="Agency FB">Another weak point of Firefly is that it does not provide the 
user with any abstraction capabilities (issue 13). </font> </p>
    <!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td>
  </tr>
  <!--msthemelist--></table>
<!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">

